    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Zenith Electronics Names a New Agency</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STEVE LOHR</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Lohr, Steve</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Zenith Electronics names Cramer-Krasselt to handle its advertising account; billings estimated at $15 million to $20 million (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Zenith Electronics, in Glenview, Ill., part of the LG Electronics unit of the LG Group, named Cramer-Krasselt in Chicago to handle its account, which had been handled on a project basis. Billings were estimated at $15 million to $20 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Zenith Electronics, in Glenview, Ill., part of the LG Electronics unit of the LG Group, named Cramer-Krasselt in Chicago to handle its account, which had been handled on a project basis. Billings were estimated at $15 million to $20 million.</p>
        <p>The decision came after a one-month review that had been narrowed to Cramer-Krasselt and Laughlin/Constable in Chicago and Milwaukee.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
